{
  "texts": [
    "Intuitively, it means that we accept the weak solution with high probabilities when the absolute diff value is lower than the T value.",
    "Once the set of DNNs is selected for the current clients, the DNNs must be loaded onto the workers.",
    "However, loading a DNN on a GPU can incur a considerable time overhead due to the launching of CUDA kernels, transfer of DNN parameters, etc.",
    "To mitigate this issue, we prefetch DNNs on GPUs.",
    "More specifically, we employ a prefetching technique based on the nearest-neighbor policy where we pre-load DNNs neighboring the currently loaded one."
  ]
}